A Game-Day must-have! 🏈😋 

INGREDIENTS

✅ 1 tablespoon olive oil
✅ 1 small onion, diced
✅ ½ pound 90% lean ground beef
✅ ½ pound bulk pork sausage
✅ 1 garlic clove, minced
✅ 1 (10-ounce) can of diced tomato and green chilies, drained
✅ 1 (15-ounce) can of chili con carne without beans
✅ 2 (8-ounce) packages of cream cheese, at room temperature
✅ 2 cups cheddar jack cheese, shredded
✅ 1 (16-ounces) FAGE Sour Cream, divided
✅ Scallion, chopped for garnish

STEPS

1. Heat a large cast iron skillet to medium-high heat, and add olive oil and onion. Cook until the onion is slightly transparent.
2. Add beef, sausage, and garlic, and crumble the meat using a slotted spoon. Cook until the meat is browned. Drain the meat and remove the excess fat.
3. Add tomato and chili to the meat and cook for an additional 15-20 minutes on medium-low heat.
4. Remove from heat and add cream cheese, jack cheese, and half of the sour cream.
5. Top with the remaining sour cream and scallions and serve with tortilla chips and vegetables.

This homemade Lemon Tahini yogurt dressing is light and versatile. 

INGREDIENTS

Dressing Ingredients:
✅ ½ cup FAGE Total 0%, 2%, or 5%
✅ 3 tablespoons lemon juice, zest of a lemon
✅ 1 tablespoon tahini
✅ 3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil
✅ ½ teaspoon garlic salt
✅ ¼ teaspoon black pepper

Ingredients for Layering Salad:
✅ Protein: egg, quinoa, chicken, steak, edamame, feta
✅ Vegetables: cucumber, tomato, red onion, shredded carrot, avocado, corn
✅ Greens: arugula, spinach, mesclun, romaine

STEPS

1. Place all dressing ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth.
2. Make your salads by adding the dressing to the bottom of the jar.
3. Next place any proteins like egg, quinoa, chicken, steak, edamame, or feta.
4. Next add vegetables like cucumber, tomato, red onion, shredded carrot, avocado, and corn.
5. Top with leafy greens like arugula, spinach, mesclun, romaine or any other greens of your choice.

The perfect bread to add to your Labor Day spread. These Za’atar Knots are soft and buttery, with just the right amount of flavor. Get recipe 👇

INGREDIENTS
✅ 2 ¼ cups self-rising flour, extra for dusting
✅ 2 cups FAGE Total 0%, 2%, or 5%, at room temperature
✅ 1 teaspoon salt
✅ ½ cup extra-virgin olive oil
✅ 1 tablespoon garlic powder
✅ 1 tablespoon Za’atar seasoning
✅ ½ cup fresh parsley, chopped
✅ ¼ cup Parmigiano cheese, grated

STEPS
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set it aside.
2. In a large bowl, stir together flour, Greek yogurt, and salt until well combined.
3. Dust flour onto a clean surface and knead the dough until smooth and pliable.
4. Cut into 8 equal pieces. Cover each dough with a damp paper towel while you work on each piece.
5. Roll each piece out into 10-inch strips and tie each strip into a knot. Tuck any ends underneath the knots. Repeat with the remaining strips.
6. Spread the knots evenly on the baking sheet, leaving room on each side of the knots.
7. In a small bowl, mix olive oil, garlic powder, Za’atar seasoning, parsley, and Parmigiano. Generously brush the oil mixture on each knot.
8. Bake for 15-18 minutes or until golden brown.
9. Serve with extra Za’atar oil or with your favorite dipping sauce.
